data.enText: the bottom part of a tree left in the ground after the rest has fallen or been cut down
the end of sth or the part that is left after the main part has been cut, broken off or worn away
the stump of a pencil
the short part of sb's leg or arm that is left after the rest has been cut off
one of the set of three vertical wooden sticks (called the stumps ) that form the wicket

data.chText: （政治家在选举前的）巡回演说
data.enText: the fact of a politician before an election going to different places and trying to get people's support by making speeches

data.chText: 那位参议员进行了一次例行的竞选巡回演说。
data.enText: The senator gave his standard stump speech.
politicians on the stump
stir your stumps
to begin to move; to hurry
to ask sb a question that is too difficult for them to answer or give them a problem that they cannot solve

data.chText: 我搞不懂了。我不知道他们怎么比我们来得还早。
data.enText: I'm stumped. I don't know how they got here before us.
Kate was stumped for words (= unable to answer) .

data.chText: （尤指愤怒或烦恼时）脚步重重地走
data.enText: to walk in a noisy, heavy way, especially because you are angry or upset

data.chText: 他嘴里嘟哝着，脚步重重地走了。
data.enText: He stumped off, muttering under his breath.
to travel around making political speeches, especially before an election

data.chText: 他在全国各地巡回演讲，争取更多的支持。
data.enText: He stumped around the country trying to build up support.

data.chText: （以球触三柱门）使（击球手）出局
data.enText: to put a batsman out of the game by touching the stumps with the ball when he or she is out of the area in which the ball can be hit
stump up (for sth)
stump up sth (for sth)
to pay money for sth
We were asked to stump up for the repairs.
Who is going to stump up the extra money?

example: The men stomped through the snow in their heavy boots

value.def: A stump is a small part of something that remains when the rest of it has been removed or broken off.

example.ex: If you have a tree stump, check it for fungus...
example.tran: 要是有树桩的话，检查一下上面有没有长菌类。

example.ex: The tramp produced a stump of candle from his deep pockets.
example.tran: 流浪汉从深口袋里掏出了一截蜡烛。

value.def: In cricket, the stumps are the three wooden sticks that are placed upright in the ground to form the wicket.
If you are stumped by a question or problem, you cannot think of any solution or answer to it.

example.ex: John is stumped by an unexpected question...
example.tran: 一个意想不到的问题把约翰难住了。

example.ex: Well, maybe I stumped you on that one.
example.tran: 好吧，也许我在那件事上使你为难了。

value.tran: 把…难住;难倒;使…一筹莫展

value.def: If you stump somewhere, you walk there with heavy steps.

example.ex: The Marshal stepped over the vacuum-cleaner and stumped out of the room.
example.tran: 元帅迈过真空吸尘器，脚步沉重地走出了房间。

value.tran: 迈着沉重的步子走;跺着脚走

value.def: If politicians stump the country or stump for a candidate, they travel around making campaign speeches before an election.

example.ex: When candidates went stumping around the country, people traveled for miles on foot, by horse, by carriage to hear them speak...
example.tran: 当竞选人在全国作巡回演说时，人们会步行、骑马或坐车数英里赶去听他们的演讲。

example.ex: He was in Georgia stumping for Senator Wyche Fowler, a Democrat.
example.tran: 他正在佐治亚州为民主党参议员威奇·福勒作巡回演说。

value.def: If politicians are on the stump, they are campaigning for an election.

example.ex: The presidential candidates are on the stump today.
example.tran: 总统候选人今天在作巡回演说。
